description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Specialist Children&#39;s Occupational Therapist &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Band 6 &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;2 vacancies - One full time 37.5 hrs and one part time 30 hours&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;PREVIOUS APPLICANTS NEED NOT APPLY&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen in our team for an OT with children’s OT experience. We are looking for an enthusiastic, motivated and experienced OT to join our well established and innovative Children’s OT service that combines the traditional roles of both health and social services children’s OT. We have recently relocated to a modern purpose built Children’s Development Centre (CDC) promoting MDT working and shared working spaces.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;The post will provide OT services to children with a wide range of disabilities. OT services will include the full range of OT input required by the children on your caseload in their homes, nurseries, schools and respite placements within Croydon. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Along with clinical work the post holder will also supervise more junior members of the team and OT students on placements and assist with and lead on service developments. Regular supervision and support will be provided.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are a dynamic, friendly and supportive team of 15 OTs, 2 OT Technical Instructors and 3 Administrators who have a wide range of skills and expertise. The service has a good reputation and we work closely with colleagues across children’s services in Health, Education, Social Services and the voluntary sector.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our integrated health and social services OT team provides you with an excellent opportunity to broaden your skills and provide a comprehensive OT service to the children of Croydon, their parents/carers and other professionals.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;ESSENTIAL REQUIREMENTS:&lt;br /&gt;- A Diploma / Degree in Occupational Therapy&lt;br /&gt;- State registration with the Health and Care Professions Council (HCPC)&lt;br /&gt;- Experience working with children with disabilities in a community OT setting&lt;br /&gt;- A valid UK driving license&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Interview: 10th December 2020&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Jo Kavanagh or Caireen McGlashan&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;(Children’s Occupational Therapy Team Managers) on 020 8274 6854 / 6850, 07812 061 381 / 07812 061 621&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
